\begin_layout Standard
Alteration of the food web of the northern range of Yellowstone National
 Park during the last century has created a natural experiment with exceptional
 potential to understand the interplay of biotic, physical,  and climatic
 controls on alternative ecosystem states.
 The landscapes of the northern range experienced dramatic changes in structure
 and function over the last century 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
before "reviewed by"
key "Council:2002qc"

\end_inset

.
 During the early 1900s, communities of willows predominated the riparian
 zones of the northern range, extending up to 40 m laterally from stream
